						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up near the Chennakēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśiva, 1567 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1489, Prābhava, Jyēshṭha śu.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to record some concessions granted for bringing under cultivation lands which had become fallow in the village Sajjaladinna which was an <hi rend="italic">Uṁbaḷi-grāma</hi> (rent free grant of a village). Mentions Rāmarāju Tirumalarājayya.</p>						

						</summary>
